furthermore I want to say thanks to Sangre, Absolute and Kabo for their special help with finding bugs and beta testing.

the map:

it is a linear surf map and has 1 Bonus

System:
when the players are spawned there is a pre timer which forgives every fail the first minute. After that minute you will get teleported to Jail after every fail.
If you are in Jail you can look up: there is another timer which teleports everyone in Jail back to spawn every 30 seconds.
After another 4 minutes (with pre timer 5 minutes) the "jailback" timer stops and you will not get back to spawn again.

Bonus:
The Bonus has a counter at the beginning. It counts the fails of 1 team. 1 team is allowed to fail 7 times (after the 7 fails every fail will teleport you to jail)
There is a secret button which can reset the fail counter ONE time for ONE team.

There are several secrets in the map. I hope you enjoy finding them ^^

surf_kalium made by Helix

Map has 4 stages

1 = very easy
2 = medium
3 = hard
4 = very hard

There is 1 bonus, can be accessed at the beginning of stage 1. Note that the teleporter between the first 2 ramps of bonus is not the end but just the escape teleporter. The end of bonus can be beaten by entering the trigger and WALK towards the end.

This map has been on my computer for 1.5 years, so in fact, yeah, it took  1.5 years to finish (also counting the many months I did nothing about it)

Finally it's here! Enjoy!

I'm being honest with you, this is my first map released. I am VERY proud of this map, because it has taken me over a month, and over 7 keyboard and 2 monitors.

This map is BIG. I didn't save the log, but I have used over 98% of the brushsides allowed and over 90% of brushes.

There is roughly 1:30-2minutesof surfing here, and THIS IS NOT MEANT TO BE A HARD MAP. Yes, the end is difficult, but that is meant to be the ONLY hard area.

I am not completely satisfied that this is worthy of a full release, so I'm just gonna call this beta1 :P

I would like to point out that this map is FULLY optimised! EVERYTHING apart from the skyboxes has been func_detail'd! This map is as optimized as it ever will be. If anyone wants to have a crack at optimizeign the map further, PM me for the .vmf

Any bugs you find please tell me, and any feedback whatsoever is great.

Have fun and tell me what you think :D

surf_jumble is a Tier 6 Staged map with 2 Stages and 4 Bonuses.

This map is what I would describe as the most confusing surf map out there today. It is heavily inspired by tricksurf routing, but in a skillsurf environment. While the routes aren't immediately intuitive, I hope to have made up for that with intuitive surf once the route is learnt by the player. If you want to learn the route for a stage/bonus, read the numbers on the corners of the ramps for the order of the surf.

Stage 1 is more straight-forward with minimal looping, whereas stage 2 has the player reusing ramps several times in different ways each pass-through.

Bonuses 1, 2, and 4 are made by myself. Bonus 3 is made by Spy Complex.
Bonus 4 is meant to be played with auto-bhop. Collect the 3 colored keys in order to pass through the respective colored walls.

Special thanks to Sam for making essentially all of the filters for my map (so I hope they work fine on every server, this has been tested extensively by myself and a few others but if there are any glaring issues it would be nice to know).
Thanks to sneaK, pretzL, and Spy Complex for testing (testers from previous versions are credited in the map hub, you guys are great too).

And thanks to Juxtapo + Hesuka for the showcase video:


Thank you to everyone who helped me stay motivated and to all those who play my map!! Enjoy!

Alright guys.  I admit that I did a horrible job on japan_v4.  I fixed spawn killing in that version and added my section from surf_oblivionv1final (level 1 from it--it's not called danger-surf lol that's just telling you what textures kill you)...  But when I did these edits I ended up making the map worse.

I was a noob then, but I think I did a good job this time.

I run a geforce6200--not a great card, and I would get 10-11 fps from spawn with nothing else running.  Japanv2 maybe 14.  Japanv6 I'd get around 17.  But this version I net up to 27 fps looking straight out from spawn.  That doesn't sound like much to most people but to me it's a huge improvement.

I'll go through my edits...

Fixed the water bug where you'd get stuck (you can still get stuck going off to the water sides but you can break out by strafing/turning hard)

added various hint/skip textures

added several areaportals in the opening areas of japan

Used a teleporter to separate the two halves of japan and used a landmark to save your position (while not perfect and the best looking, it cuts lag big time)

lowered the height of spawn

moved bottom section of the map with monkeydie's original credits which was lagging me like a bitch

glass should be bulletproof to awps, if not tell me.

squeezed the skybox more (raised the bottom I mean)

Added level 2 of oblivionv1final and put level 1 back in also.  Also added area portals in these sections

Finishing my sections gives you awps, both autos, and several textures explaining why I redid this.  You can also directly port to either spawn or the sniping top area.

Added a direct portal to top where if you cheat in the second section, you port in water on top.

Changed a freakin' horde of textures into func_detail to shorten compile time (I forget what else that does...) and I might have done other things I can't remember right now.

Things I did badly though...  I could have done the landmark better, there's a bad looking texture at the end of the water, I added several hint/skip textures that weren't needed in a few areas.  One of the reasons I added func_detail stuff is because I was getting a vvis error when I compiled.  Actually, this version gave me a vrad error, but the water works so I don't care.  It's 8mb but I don't care about file size (find oblivionv1final and you'll see why).

And I know some people will hate me for doing this (some already hate me for v4...).  But I loved this map back in the day, but I couldn't play it because of the lag on my machine.  So I redid it again...  As I said in the final credits area, I will do another version without my sections.  I just can't do it right now, as I've got college and a crap load of maps to make for my clan.

And before someone says it, I'm not a member of Dark Arena (which is now Underground Central... which removed their surf server).

Added oon to the end of the map name because someone may have already made a v7...

If there is an error tell me.  If you need to decompile this, tell me and I'll tell you how to fix it and save you some time.  Actually, I could just give you the vmf...

If I remember something important I'll post here.  Added push platforms to compensate for the lack of height.
